Package fluent.ly

Interface lazy<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - JD
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.function.Supplier<@Nullable T>
    public interface lazy<@Nullable T>
extends java.util.function.Supplier<@Nullable T>
    A class for lazy, memoizing evaluation of objects of arbitrary type. The evaluation must never return null. Main purpose is for lazy initialization as in static final lazy<Collection<Thing>> things = lazy.get(() -> as.list(// new Thing("one"), // new Thing("two") // )); use things.get() to obtain value; it would be computed only on first call, and cached hence after

    This class is not expected to be instantiated by clients; use as demonstrated above
